name: Box
description: Boxing training is a form of martial arts and fitness program that focuses on the sport of boxing. It involves learning and practicing various punches, including jabs, crosses, hooks, and uppercuts, as well as footwork, head movement, and defense techniques. Boxing training typically takes place in a gym setting, with participants using heavy bags, speed bags, and other equipment to improve their technique and power.

training.name: Body Combat
training.description: Body Combat is a high-energy, martial arts-inspired fitness program. It combines moves and techniques from various styles such as karate, boxing, taekwondo, tai chi, and muay thai to provide a full-body workout. Participants perform choreographed routines set to high-energy music, and the program is typically led by a instructor. Body Combat focuses on building strength, endurance, and coordination, and can also help to improve cardiovascular fitness and burn calories.

training.description: Leg training involves exercises that target the muscles of the lower body, including the quadriceps, hamstrings, glutes, and calves. These exercises can be performed with bodyweight, resistance bands, dumbbells, barbells, or machines, and can range from squats, lunges, deadlifts, calf raises, and more.
